  "commentary": "With SPX at 7093 sitting above the GEX flip at 6995 but below the massive +7237M gamma wall at 7200, dealers are long gamma and will mechanically sell this rally as it approaches 7200. The thick positive gamma clusters at 7100/7150/7200 create a magnetic pull zone where mean reversion forces should dominate, while the negative gamma pocket at 7115 represents a minor amplification zone that could see accelerated moves if breached.\n\nKey levels: Watch for dealer selling pressure to intensify as we approach the 7150-7200 zone, with 7100 acting as the primary support magnet given its +5027M gamma wall.\n\nBottom line: Expect the market to get pulled back toward 7100-7150 range with resistance building near 7200.",
